TY  - JOUR
T1  - Optimal Stock Depletion Policies with Stochastic Lives
AU  - Albright, S. Christian
Y1  - 1976/04/01
PY  - 1976
DA  - 1976/04/01
N1  - doi: 10.1287/mnsc.22.8.852
DO  - 10.1287/mnsc.22.8.852
T2  - Management Science
JF  - Management Science
JO  - Management Science
SP  - 852
EP  - 857
VL  - 22
IS  - 8
PB  - INFORMS
N2  - This paper deals with the optimal issuing sequence of units, say batteries, from storage to the field when field lives are stochastic. Several appealing forms of the field life survival probability F?(y?x) are given when the battery has been on the shelf a length of time x. These forms are used to investigate the optimally of LIFO (issue youngest) or FIFO (issue oldest) policies in two basic models. These models correspond to issuing batteries either according to a possibly random schedule (the independent case) or one after another as the successive batteries fail (the dependent case).
AB  - This paper deals with the optimal issuing sequence of units, say batteries, from storage to the field when field lives are stochastic. Several appealing forms of the field life survival probability F?(y?x) are given when the battery has been on the shelf a length of time x. These forms are used to investigate the optimally of LIFO (issue youngest) or FIFO (issue oldest) policies in two basic models. These models correspond to issuing batteries either according to a possibly random schedule (the independent case) or one after another as the successive batteries fail (the dependent case).
